comments.undefined: The STORM (STOrytelling and Metaphors) ontology examines metaphors and their connections to storytelling theories by influential scholars. More specifically, the ontology focuses on metaphors found in Shakespearean works and the ways in which they reflect storytelling aspects. With this project we attempt to demonstrate that metaphors do not only throw light on the conscious or subconscious narrative methods employed by the author, but that they may also provide insight into the main ideas of a story. Ultimately, we argue that the topic of a story may be extracted by the metaphors found in the work.
